                    <div class="bg-light border-bottom border-5 border-primary rounded p-4 mb-4">
                        <p class="text-dark mb-2">
                            The Board of Directors of the Connecticut Council of Masajid (CCM) and the Islamic Center of Hamden (ICH) is composed of dedicated community leaders and representatives from local masajid. Their mission is to ensure that all services, including the operations of Paradise Avenue Muslim Cemetery, are managed with integrity, transparency, and in full accordance with Islamic principles.



                        </p>
                        <span class="text-primary">Paradise Avenue Muslim Cemetery</span>
                    </div>
                    <p class="mb-5">
                        Guided by Shariah and community trust, the Board oversees policy decisions, financial matters, and long-term planning. Their commitment ensures that the cemetery remains a sacred and dignified space for the burial of Muslims, while also supporting broader religious, social, and educational goals of the Muslim community across Connecticut.

                    </p>
